FBIS4-54519 "dreeu084_h_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-084 Daily Report 1 May 1994 HUNGARY Boross Meets Slovak Counterpart in Komarom Boross Meets Slovak Counterpart in Komarom LD0105215294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network in Hungarian 2100 GMT 1 May 94 LD0105215294 Budapest Kossuth Radio Network Hungarian BFN [Text] The Hungarian and Slovak prime ministers have met in Komarom. As planned originally, no agreement has been signed at the talks between Peter Boross and Jozef Moravcik. However, the two discussed the situation of the Hungarian minority in Slovakia, the Boes [Gabcikovo] Dam, the elimination of double taxation, and the opening of new border crossing points. At the joint news conference it was said that the greatest achievement of these Hungarian-Slovak prime ministerial talks is that a new phase will begin in bilateral relations. The meeting made possible the settlement of the disputed issues at a later stage, it was said at the press briefing.
